# {{.ProviderShortName}} Provider

A [Terraform](https://www.terraform.io) provider for
[MXroute](https://mxroute.com) email hosting. It manages an MXroute account
through the MXroute REST API (`api.mxroute.com`), turning mailboxes, forwarders,
spam policy, and reseller accounts into declarative, version-controlled
configuration.

It covers the account end to end:

- **Domains** — mail domains (`mxroute_domain`), with their DNS records and
  ownership-verification key exposed as data sources (`mxroute_dns`,
  `mxroute_verification_key`).
- **Mailboxes** — email accounts (`mxroute_email_account`) with write-only
  passwords, storage quota, and daily send limits.
- **Routing** — forwarders/aliases (`mxroute_forwarder`), domain pointers
  (`mxroute_pointer`), and the per-domain catch-all policy
  (`mxroute_catch_all` — deliver, reject, or discard unmatched mail).
- **Spam** — per-domain spam settings (`mxroute_spam_settings`) and
  blacklist/whitelist entries (`mxroute_spam_blacklist_entry`,
  `mxroute_spam_whitelist_entry`).
- **Reseller** — packages and users (`mxroute_reseller_package`,
  `mxroute_reseller_user`) for accounts with reseller access.

Read-only **data sources** mirror each area — singular lookups
(`mxroute_domain`, `mxroute_reseller_user`, …) and listings (`mxroute_domains`,
`mxroute_email_accounts`, `mxroute_forwarders`, `mxroute_pointers`,
`mxroute_spam_blacklist`, `mxroute_spam_whitelist`, `mxroute_quota`, …).

## Requirements

- **Terraform >= 1.11.** The `mxroute_email_account` and `mxroute_reseller_user`
  resources use [write-only arguments][wo], which Terraform added in 1.11. The
  provider has no other version-gated features, so 1.11 is the baseline for the
  whole provider.

[wo]: https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/language/resources/ephemeral#write-only-arguments

## Authentication

The provider authenticates to the MXroute REST API with three values. Each may
be set as a provider argument or read from the environment, so credentials can
be kept out of configuration:

| Provider argument | Environment variable | Description |
|-------------------|----------------------|-------------|
| `server` | `MXROUTE_SERVER` | Mail server hostname (e.g. `heracles.mxrouting.net`). |
| `username` | `MXROUTE_USERNAME` | DirectAdmin username. |
| `api_key` | `MXROUTE_API_KEY` | API key (sensitive; never logged). |

Mailbox and reseller-user passwords are **write-only**: they are sent to the API
but never stored in Terraform state. To rotate one, set the new value and bump
the paired `*_wo_version` argument.

See the [MXroute API documentation](https://api.mxroute.com/docs) for the
underlying endpoints.

